emulib.plugins.compiler

Interface Compiler

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Plugin
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCompiler

    public interface Compiler
extends Plugin
    This interface is the core for compiler plug-in types. These plug-ins should implement this interface once and only once.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static interface  Compiler.CompilerListener
      This is an interface that should be implemented by the emuStudio, and/or other plug-ins that want to process the output of the compiler.

                String outputFileName)

      • compile

        boolean compile(String inputFileName)
        Compile an input file into the output file. Output file name is derived by the compiler itself. Usually, the extension of the input file is replaced by another one, denoting compiled file. It is compiler-specific.
        Parameters:
        inputFileName - name of the input file (source code)
        Returns:
        true if compile was successful, false otherwise

      • getLexer

        LexicalAnalyzer getLexer(Reader in)
        Get a lexical analyzer of the compiler. It is used by main module for syntax highlighting. In the compilation process the compiler should use own, independent lexical analyzer.
        Parameters:
        in - Reader object of the document - source code.
        Returns:
        lexical analyzer object

      • getProgramStartAddress

        int getProgramStartAddress()
        Gets starting address of compiled source. It is (or can be) called only after compilation process. It should return the first occurrence of compiled program. The word "address" can be replaced by a term "offset from 0". One step in address has size of one byte. It means that return value should not be related to operating memory units and should not deliberate techniques used in operating memory, e.g. banking.
        Returns:
        address of program's first occurrence

      • getSourceSuffixList

        SourceFileExtension[] getSourceSuffixList()
        Gets the list of supported source file name suffixes. The list is case insensitive. This method is called only once by emuStudio.
        Returns:
        list of supported source file name suffixes
